					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You have to be sure to don't use the same variable in NMI that in the game logic (including Temp variables and so on, the only exeption can be the flags and the PPU data, so if you have a PPU buffer, the "correct" way to do this is input a flag to say if the buffer is "ready" or not to be updated), you also have to be sure to push all the registers A, X and Y at the begining of the interrupt to resore them at the end, it's also recomanded to write at least twice to $2005 and once to $2000 per VBlank (but it may not be 100% obligatory).
<br />Else, this shouldnt be a real problem exept about the speed of your programm.
<br />
<br />If everithing above is done I can't see what's going up. Be especially carefull with your variables/buffers.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
